    "impact": "This can cause incorrect accounting in the Fenwick tree, potentially affecting subsequent deposit processing or claim operations.",
    "paths": ["1. User has pending deposit request", "2. Oracle report is submitted before cancellation", "3. cancelDepositRequest uses wrong index", "4. Fenwick tree state corrupted"]
  },
  {
    "id": "F-025",
    "severity": "Medium",
    "confidence": "high",
    "title": "ShareModule claimableSharesOf unbounded loop vulnerability",
    "locations": ["modules/ShareModule.sol:116-132", "modules/ShareModule.sol:234-250"],
    "claim": "claimableSharesOf and claimShares iterate over all assets and all deposit queues with no pagination or gas limits.",
    "impact": "If the vault has many assets and queues, these functions can exceed gas limits and revert, preventing users from claiming their shares. Additionally, this creates a griefing attack surface where the owner can add many empty queues/assets to make claiming impossible.",
    "paths": ["1. Owner adds many assets with many queues", "2. User attempts to claim shares", "3. Operation reverts due to out-of-gas"]
  },
  {
